contentrichtext.text: In [[telecommunication]], a '''voice frequency primary patch bay''' (VF) is a patching facility that provides the first appearance of local-[[User (telecommunications)|user]] VF circuits in the [[technical control facility]] (TCF). The VF primary [[patch bay]] provides patching, [http://wiktionary.org/wiki/Transwiki:Monitoring monitoring], and testing for all VF circuits. Signals will have various levels and [[Signalling (telecommunication)|signaling]] schemes depending on the user [[terminal equipment]]. ==References== *{{FS1037C MS188}} [[Category:Telecommunications equipment]] {{telecomm-stub}}
